        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1973-03-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1973-03-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="91"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                <head>91. Memorandum From the President’s Assistant for National Security Affairs
                        (<persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Kissinger</persName>)<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d91fn1">Source: National Archives, <persName corresp="#p_NRM_1"
                            >Nixon</persName> Presidential Materials, <gloss target="#t_NSC_1"
                            >NSC</gloss> Files, Box 721, Country Files—Europe—<gloss
                            target="#t_USSR_1">USSR</gloss>, Vol. XXVIII. Confidential. A copy was
                        sent to the Executive Director, <gloss target="#t_CIEP_1"
                        >CIEP</gloss>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1973-03-31">March 31, 1973</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list>
                    <head>FOR</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of the Treasury</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Agriculture</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Commerce</item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Public Statements on Soviet Emigration and <gloss target="#t_MFN_1"
                            >MFN</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <p>The President has directed that Administration officials planning statements on
                    the subjects of Soviet emigration policy and the issue of Most Favored Nation
                    treatment for the Soviet Union submit the text of the proposed statement to the
                    White House for clearance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed corresp="#p_KHA_1">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KHA_1">Henry A. Kissinger</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
